{subhead} Amiga Survivor Magazine Survives{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

Dear Amiga Survivors,
{p} {p}
After a couple of months break, Amiga Survivor Magazine returns with a
brand new issue.  We are now settled in our new offices, and the newly
designed magazine finally makes a comeback with the best issue yet.
{p} {p}
The new, full-color cover'd A4 magazine has just been released with pages
of the latest news, reviews and previews of all things Amiga.
{p} {p}
We have a special 4-page EXCLUSIVE preview of Digital Images' forthcoming
conversion of WipEout 2097, including weapon and craft details and an
exclusive interview with the man behind the conversion; Stuart Walker.
There are full reviews of NetConnect v2, Kang-Fu, APC&TCP volumes 4 & 6.
Tons of previews including:  The Prophet & Phoenix Fighters from Alive
Mediasoft, Wildtracks, Pinball Pro, Abduction, Diablos Land, MegaPolice,
The Last Seal, and updaates of Spcestation 3000, Hex, The Holy Trinity and
more!
{p} {p}
Plus, we'll have the usual articles, such as The Fifth Column, The
Trashcan, Aminet Ramble, Web Watch and all that malarkey.  We're also
introducing our new feature, a Retro page which looks back over the last
few years of the Amiga's livelihood.  PLUS!  We've also got (another) BRAND
NEW LOOK courtesy of our cover artist; Stephen Thwaites.  You'll have to
See it to Believe it!
{p} {p}
Visit the official Amiga Survivor Website at:{p}
{link http://www.crystal-software.com/AmigaSurvivor/survindex.html}http://www.crystal-software.com/AmigaSurvivor/survindex.html{end}
